+ JOB Card Placement
} The JOB Card is placed immediately following the line where the cursor
} left when you pressed ENTER.  Normally, you will leave the cursor on t
} command line where you entered "JOBC" (unless you have assigned this c
} to a PF Key).  The command line, if the screen is at "top of data", is
} as line 0, and the JOB Card will be placed at the start of the data.
} cursor was left on line 1, JOBC will assume line 0.
}
} If the cursor was left elsewhere, the JOB Card is normally placed afte
} line, but a warning is given on the JOB Card panel, and you can change
} line number. Enter 0 or 1 to have the JOB Card placed at the start of
}
} The command line when the screen is NOT at top of data is taken to be
} the first line of data on the screen.
}
}
                        +For more information press%ENTER}
